   =20
      GTII?!?
   =20
 =20
Global Tech Industries Group Inc. is a small public company that trades ove=
r the counter and=C2=A0is, as far as I can tell, in the business of being a=
 meme stock? It has no revenue, two employees,=C2=A0a strong generic name a=
nd a market capitalization of about $300 million. The overview of its busin=
ess in its most recent quarterly report notes that it was named Western Exp=
loration Inc.=C2=A0from 1980 to 1990, Nugget Exploration Inc. from 1990 to =
1999, GoHealthMD Inc. from 1999 to 2004 and Tree Top Industries from 2004 u=
ntil 2017, when it settled on the current name. Just in 2021 it signed deal=
s to get=C2=A0into businesses that included buying and selling gold in Duba=
i, =E2=80=9Cfull scope optometry=E2=80=9D in the Bronx, diagnostic medical =
care on the internet, cryptocurrency trading on the blockchain, tokenizing =
fine art, green energy, online learning tools, and mining in Chile. In 2022=
=C2=A0it signed a deal to =E2=80=9Cdevelop a Chinatown art district within =
the Company=E2=80=99s planned Metaverse.=E2=80=9D There is more, but I will=
 stop here.Here is the =E2=80=9CNews=E2=80=9D section of its website, which=
 is dominated these days by one transaction: Global Tech Industries is tryi=
ng to pay a crypto dividend. =E2=80=9CHolders of the Company=E2=80=99s comm=
on stock will receive four (4) Shiba Inu tokens for every one (1) share of =
the Company=E2=80=99s common stock,=E2=80=9D says a May 3 press release, th=
ough other press releases call it a =E2=80=9CShibu Ino=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=
=9CShibu Inu=E2=80=9D token so really who knows. One Shiba Inu token is wor=
th about=C2=A0$0.0000103 these days, give or take a zero or two, making fou=
r of them worth, you know, a small fraction of a penny.Why do this? Well, w=
hy do anything? But there are some obvious advantages, for a meme stock, to=
 paying a dividend in crypto:=09People like Shiba Inu memes and cryptocurre=
ncy, so you=E2=80=99ll attract some attention, which might make your stock =
go up.=09The dividend will be paid on the Beyond Blockchain platform that G=
TII bought in 2021 and then  sold in 2022 for =E2=80=9Ccash payment of $25,=
000, and a continuing 10% interest from Parabolic Technologies which will b=
e distributed in the form of a proprietary token.=E2=80=9D If you own a sta=
ke in a blockchain platform, you might as well drum up business for it by o=
ffering your shareholders a tiny amount of money to sign up for accounts on=
 that platform.=C2=A0=09It is a general odd fact of US public companies tha=
t it is   hard to get to know your shareholders: Your relationship with sha=
reholders is intermediated by brokers and =E2=80=9Cstreet name=E2=80=9D own=
ership, so most companies don=E2=80=99t have good lists of their shareholde=
rs. Having a list of your most enthusiastic, meme-curious shareholders seem=
s valuable. So  many of the  press releases that GTII has put out are basic=
ally urging people to send in their forms to get this dividend. The point i=
s not just distributing the dividend, it is also about getting the forms ba=
ck to know how to contact shareholders.=09If you are a short seller who has=
 borrowed GTII stock to sell it, now you have to deliver four Shiba Inu tok=
ens per share back to your lender, I guess, which   seems like a   pain, an=
d making life painful for short sellers is a key meme-stock aim.
