h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;"> before</a>.=C2=A0Traditional web platforms have =E2=80=9Cn=
etwork effects=E2=80=9D where a thing is more valuable the more people use =
it; this creates incentives to join the big platforms. But web3 platforms h=
ave =E2=80=9Ctoken effects=E2=80=9D where early adopters get a lot of token=
s that represent a sort of equity in the platform; this creates incentives =
to join platforms early. So web3 projects tend to have two=C2=A0related com=
ponents:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; marg=
in: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">A decentralized distribut=
ed system that (you hope) does something useful, and</li>=09<li style=3D"ma=
rgin-bottom: 5px;">A token that enables you to use the system and that goes=
 up in value when the system becomes more popular.</li></ol><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 16px 0;">The attraction of any web3 project, early on, will be a combi=
nation of those two things: You get to use a thing that you think is good, =
and also the early adopters will get rich if it takes off. In a frenzied cr=
ypto boom, the Ponzi element =E2=80=94=C2=A0the prospect of getting rich if=
 the thing takes off =E2=80=94=C2=A0will tend to dominate, and most people =
will be in most projects for the money, not for the utility of the underlyi=
ng thing. But=C2=A0<em>eventually that has to flip</em>; Ponzis can=E2=80=
=99t work forever. If your project gets established enough, if it offers re=
al utility, if people are buying tokens to do the thing that it does rather=
 than to speculate on the tokens going up, then you can transition from=C2=
=A0Ponzi economics to just regular old economics. People will buy the token=
 because they can use it to do useful stuff, not because they hope more peo=
ple will pile in and they can sell it for a profit.</p><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">This flip will probably happen gradually over time, but it might b=
e crystallized in a broad market crash, and then you might go around saying=
 things like =E2=80=9Csometimes having to flush out people who are just in =
it for the money, that=E2=80=99s just the system self-correcting,=E2=80=9D =
and that will make sense. I am not sure it does here.</p><table class=3D"he=
